node.text:
Musselman Library will be closed on Thursday, August 27 and will re-open on Friday morning, August 28, at 8am. During this time the library will undergo an aggressive cleaning.
.
We are closing the library for this 24-hour period because of repeated breaches in mask-wearing protocol and disregard for the physical distancing rules. Masks are required at all times, and only one person is allowed at a table. 
The following exceptions will be made to the closure:

1. Students and faculty whose courses meet in the library classroom (Room 018) or have classes scheduled in Special Collections, may swipe into the building with their ID card.
2. Muss-to-go, the library’s “grab and go” request service for books will be available until 5pm. Students and faculty may swipe in to pick up their books but must leave immediately.
3. Anyone with a reservation in Special Collections or an in-person appointment with a librarian may enter the building with their ID until 5pm.
.
We are #bettertogether, but you must do your part to help keep everyone safe this semester! #maskon 
#socialdistance

node.text:
Since the pandemic, one of the things that we—especially the pious and the religious—yearn for is going to church.

Of course, God is everywhere. But prayer is much different when done with a community, in a Holy Mass, amidst the serenity of a holy place. Before, we could even afford to miss this holy obligation. But suddenly, after months of deprivation, we miss that kind of worship, the Holy Eucharist, the echoing words of wisdom. We miss this kind of communion with God. Suddenly, we just can’t wait to step inside a church again.

In this lyric essay, Sisang Batute expresses her deep yearning for this, particularly for the Holy Eucharist. Here’s her full story—https://scribblorywriters.wordpress.com/2020/08/25/to-the-great-i-am/

node.text:
هو اسم آخر لغسيل الكلى، يساعد على تنقية الدم من شخص لا تعمل كليته بشكل طبيعي. يمكن لغسيل الدم أيضاً أن يوازن المعادن المهمة في الدم، كما يمكن أن يجعلك تشعر بتحسن جسدي، لكن الغسيل الدموي ليس علاجاً للفشل الكلوي. 
Another name for dialysis, it helps purify the blood of a person whose kidneys are not working normally. Hemodialysis can also balance important minerals in your blood. While it can make you feel much better physically, hemodialysis is not a cure for kidney failure.

node.text:
Kan ik door een gezonde leefstijl voorkomen dat ik ziek word?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Ja… en … ook een beetje nee, helaas bestaat er geen interventie die garantie biedt dat u het coronavirus niet oploopt of er ernstig ziek van wordt. Ook niet een gezonde leefstijl. De beste manier om te voorkomen dat u het virus oploopt werd in de vorige post behandeld (houd je aan de maatregelen).
 
Maar er is steeds meer bekend over het belang van een gezonde leefstijl en de gezondheidswinst die daarbij hoort. U loopt minder risico om ziek te worden als u een gezonde leefstijl heeft. Dit geldt niet alleen voor COVID19, maar ook voor een scala aan andere ziektebeelden. Er valt veel voor te zeggen om juist nu goed voor uzelf te zorgen. Onderdeel daarvan is: gezonde voeding, voldoende beweging en slaap, sociale verbinding, zingeving en ontspanning (niet te veel stress en angst).
 
Ook hier geldt gezond verstand. Als we de vergelijking met een auto maken; een goed onderhouden auto krijgt minder snel problemen met remmen of een ander onderdeel. Zorg dus ook goed voor uw eigen lichaam en geest.

Ataukah kita terlena dan abai terhadap protokol kesehatan?

Jaga jarak aman saat sedang berada di ruang publik, olahraga dan makan teratur dengan gizi seimbang, rajin cuci tangan, dan tingkatkan imun dengan mengkonsumsi suplemen herbal tambahan
Dan yang terpenting jangan lupa agar rajin beribadah dan berdoa

Stay safe, sanak

S02E28: Advocating For Radical Enviro Change While Living Package Free with Joy Morgan, @joytotheworldmorgan 🌞🌎 #wildlifepreservation #renewableenergy

Joy Morgan makes a QWTChrises pitstop on her interdimensional road trip journey between Brooklyn and Portland to advocate for radical environmental change. On a personal quest to turn New Jersey’s Pinelands National Reserve into a National Monument, Joy discusses setting up cameras to watch snake dens, as The Chrises encourage her to capture the Jersey Devil. With still so much more to learn about public land management, Joy suggests some low cost ways to upgrade urban planning— including permeable sidewalk pavers to replenish its natural aqueducts with rain water. Joy addresses listener questions about the waste produced from plastic vs. reusable water bottles, and how the @Guppyfriend prevents microplastic pollution that results from laundering synthetic garments. The Eco-Inspiration To All talks about the upcoming Marketplace Of The Future, an innovative, interactive, and Zelda-esque World Fair of Tomorrow. Last but not least, Joy encourages everyone to do tiny, little things to make big changes such as buying reusable and compostable products from @PackageFreeShop, and repurposing grocery vegetable bags to cover and store food.

🌏 Special Guest: Joy Morgan, @joytotheworldmorgan
🤲 Community Cause of the Week: Save The Waves, @savethewavescoalition

node.text:
Applying for unemployment benefits during a pandemic can be scary, confusing, and hopeless. Not only is there a sort of stigma around reaching out for financial help, but often unemployment departments have convoluted processes for determining unemployment insurance (benefits) eligibility. The CARES Act signed by Congress in April extends unemployment benefits to those who would not usually qualify, such as self-employed workers, college students, and independent contractors. Although stimulus talks continue to stall on Capitol Hill, it is important to know if YOU qualify for stimulus and unemployment payments once guidelines are set. Visit your state's unemployment department website and the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau website for frequently asked questions about how to qualify for coronavirus aid!

For those of you unfamiliar with this artist, here's a little history...
Frida Kahlo was a Mexican painter known for her many portraits, self-portraits, and works inspired by the nature and artifacts of Mexico. Inspired by the country's popular culture, she employed a naïve folk art style to explore questions of identity, postcolonialism, gender, class, and race in Mexican society.

🇪🇸 El ser humano cree que siempre que haga algo benéfico a otro, que ganas puntos y puede cobrar o sacar estes puntos cuando quieres. Pero la realidad es muy distinta. Ninguno te debe nada, tú tienes que hacer las cosas sin esperar nada en retorno y tampoco cobrar o culpar alguno por tu vida. Tu haces tu! 🇬🇧 Human beings tend to believe that when they do something good to someone, that they collect points, points that can be withdrawn when they want to. But the truth is far from that. No one owns you a shit, you gotta do things without expecting anything back and neither call out or blame someone for the life you live. You do you!

node.text:
Zion 🙌 Utah's first national park and quite the beauty
•
This trip was special because I got to introduce Zion to @littlemissonshine and @lombard.26 and take @joelguzman3 on his first camping adventure 🏕 It did reach 110 degrees...but that's when the river and lake came in handy! 
•
Did you know...
🌎 Four life zones exist inside the park: riparian, woodland, Coniferous forest, and desert
🌎 Evidence of Zion’s earliest inhabitants dates back over 8,000 years
🌎 32 species of amphibians/reptiles, 8 species of fish, and 289 species of birds, and 79 mammals call the park home 
🌎 The park is considered to have the most extensive plant diversity in the entire state with over 800 species native to the area
•
So let's take care of nature by following fire restrictions, not feeding/approaching wildlife, practicing leave no trace, and only bringing home souvenirs from the gift shop. ✌

node.text: This is my Moms hospital room since Sunday morning. She was running a fever, having problems breathing and tested positive for covid-19. Her fever is gone, but is still having a hard time breathing and needs some oxygen assistance.  She can’t have any visitors, but thankfully she’s able to talk to me on the phone for a few minutes at a time.  I am so thankful I can still hear her voice ❤️ Asking for prayers for her, that she improves quickly, can go home soon to her husband who is getting tested today and he hopefully will test negative.  WEAR YOUR MASK!  SOCIAL DISTANCE!  THIS IS REAL! 🙏🏻🙏🏻🙏🏻🙏🏻 I LOVE YOU MOM!!!! You kicked breast cancers ass, you survived a brain aneurysm and you will kick covid to the curb!! node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Anytown Las Vegas on August 26, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'so WHY ARE RACIAL DISPARITIES IN COVID-19 EVEN HAPPENING? Let's talk about accessibility to healthcare. According to the Center for Disease Control, (CDC), "People from some racial and ethnic minority groups are more likely to be uninsured than white counterparts. Healthcare access can also be limited for these groups by many other factors, such as lack of transportation, child care, or ability to take time off of work; communication and language barriers; cultural differences between patients and providers and historical and current discrimination in healthcare system."'.

Photo by Anytown Las Vegas on August 26, 2020. Image may contain: text that says '"The real drivers of the coronavirus are unjust policies and unhealthy settings not people's genetic makeup, characteristics, or, necessarily, hygiene and social distancing behaviors." Dr. Zinzi Bailey and J. Robin Moon, both epidemiologists from Duke University. "Aside from a healthcare system that is inherently biased towards ethnic minority groups, this bias. bias stretches into the workforce even before these groups get the chance to walk into a hospital. 41% frontline workers are Black and Non-Black people of color. Workplace outbreak is a leading cause of the spread of COVID-19 leaving these overrepresented minority front liners at a disproportionate risk."'.

Photo by Anytown Las Vegas on August 26, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'IT GETS WORSE According to the Pardee RAND graduate school, "Calculations show that white workers have an average maximum unemployment benefit of $463 and Black workers $423, a difference of. of $40. Maybe $40 does not sound like much, but over 26 weeks of benefits, it. adds up to 1,040. That's nearly the size of the stimulus checks ($1,200) sent.out as part of the CARES Act..'.

Photo by Anytown Las Vegas on August 26, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'WHAT CAN YOU DO ABOUT IT? Wear a mask. If 99% of people wore masks in public, approximately 33,000 deaths could be avoided by October 1st, including these disproportionately affected minority groups.' Share COVID-19 prevention information, along with any resources you find on the matter, like this post. Connect people with resources. Share free or low cost services with others spread housing, food, testing, and mental health resources if you have the information. Your voice has power Work together. The virus doesn't discriminate, neither should you.'.

Photo by Anytown Las Vegas on August 26, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'YOUTH QUOTE "Covid-19 has created a clear line within the: U.S to separate who is seen as worthy and who isn't. Black and Latinx communities oftentimes have little access to health care and are essential workers. Those who are not in those communities are more likely to benefit from treatment, survive, and be able to get back to work with the health care they have. The economy may be starting again but at the expense of thousands of Black and Latinx communities." Sanniyah Haye.'.

Set up an Inflow Plan 2. Review Common Areas & Personal Work Space 3. Stagger Shifts & Lunch Breaks 4. Avoid Large Gatherings 5. Install Plexiglass Barriers Where Needed 6. See Clients By Appointment Only 7. Opt for Continued Remote Work GOODSENSE GROUP in collaboration with Peter A. Gall Law Corporation'.

node.text:
Day Three of our BACK TO IT! After COVID-19 series is all about staying physically apart. ⁣
⁣
We understand not all jobs can be completed from home. These tips will help you stay organized and in control of safe Social Distance procedures at work. ⁣
⁣
𝟏. 𝐒𝐞𝐭 𝐮𝐩 𝐚𝐧 𝐈𝐧𝐟𝐥𝐨𝐰 𝐏𝐥𝐚𝐧 - To avoid staff and customers crossing paths, place directional arrows and signs to direct people to stay on the left vs right side, and to designate doors for entry and exit.⁣
⁣
𝟐. 𝐑𝐞𝐯𝐢𝐞𝐰 𝐂𝐨𝐦𝐦𝐨𝐧 𝐀𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐬 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐏𝐞𝐫𝐬𝐨𝐧𝐚𝐥 𝗪𝐨𝐫𝐤 𝐒𝐩𝐚𝐜𝐞 - Kitchen, Cafeteria, Elecators, Stairways, and Washrooms can experience congestion throughout the day. It’s important to implement social distancing, one way directional paths, and a fixed occupancy limit in each space with a thorough cleaning schedule. For work spaces, make sure everyone is 2 meters apart at all times. Space out desks or stagger shifts.⁣
⁣
𝟑. 𝐒𝐭𝐚𝐠𝐠𝐞𝐫 𝐒𝐡𝐢𝐟𝐭𝐬 & 𝐋𝐮𝐧𝐜𝐡 𝐁𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐤𝐬 - Staggering shifts can greatly reduce congestion in common spaces, and lack of personal space in day to day work areas. It also helps reduce employees risk on public transit during peak hours. Assigning lunch break times to various areas of the workplace will keep social distancing and capacity under control. ⁣
⁣
𝟒. 𝐀𝐯𝐨𝐢𝐝 𝐋𝐚𝐫𝐠𝐞 𝐆𝐚𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐫𝐢𝐧𝐠𝐬 - Do not have large boardroom meetings, parties or get togethers at any time. ⁣If you must, maintain social distance and wear masks.
⁣
𝟓. 𝐈𝐧𝐬𝐭𝐚𝐥𝐥 𝐏𝐥𝐞𝐱𝐢𝐠𝐥𝐚𝐬𝐬 𝐁𝐚𝐫𝐫𝐢𝐞𝐫𝐬 𝗪𝐡𝐞𝐫𝐞 𝐍𝐞𝐞𝐝𝐞𝐝 - This is especially handy if you work face to face with customers, or cannot properly social distance at work. ⁣
⁣

node.text: Just step on it a few more time and you have my expression 😱🤪😓😬😷🤢🤮
@woolytoofles how it can be so I don’t know but the bad news keeps coming.
@sidewalkface it’s really hard to keep track with this onslaught of BAD
The news is more surreal every day.
@boris.sees.faces Yes. Totally vital! At least art never stops. ❤️ Thank you Boris.
😊⭐👍 ... To create and appreciate the creations of others is certain to bring a distraction and above all gives a positive vibe ... And with a year 2020 full of negative elements, it's almost vital!
@animaytey I so wish I could make that happen. He certainly is a talker! 🍻
Haha I want to see this one talking!
@arknark that’s so nice! Thank you and likewise! ✨
You're the best. So glad we found eachother ❤️
@aongarcia Thank you Ann! Love your comment. It’s like a little play.
Great as usual,  singing,  ohhhh mY papa.  To me, U were so wonderful ...Eddie Fisher. I hated the sentimental drips. Good use of plastique
@ottgerman Yes. He wants things to be the way they used to be
@sidewalkface and he knows they will never be.
@ottgerman the good three-dimension days are not coming back.
This poor fellow is losing it.
Love all of your sentiments—and so well put!
I May Destroy You is so good on so many levels 🖤💜💙 I thought it highly thought provoking 💓🖤💓
Good advice. You would find ways to make art with other things like trees and branches, instead of plastic. 🙂🙂
😍🎨👏👏 Amén dear Caren., dont stop. I love every creation!!!☄
😍🎨👏👏 Amén dear Caren., dont stop. I love every creation!!!☄

Sidewalk Face 1043. Me reading the news. I used the same headline for SWF 1026. I could use it every day.
•
Creativity is an act against reality. Or maybe not against but a way to name it, cope with it and ultimately transform it. It’s very powerful. I get my greatest healing from enjoying the abundant creativity of others. There’s no end! There’s not enough time to enjoy it all. Music inspires me and heals me. All creativity does. We just finished HBO’s I May Destroy You. Such a brilliant show. I really enjoyed looking forward to it each week. When I see work that bold and confident it makes me want to push further. Let’s see if I can make some weirder faces!
•
•
One more thing. Don’t litter. Ever! Sure it gives me stuff to play with but come on! This guy might be yelling because he’s supposed to be in the trash. And maybe he would like to stop being single use plastic.

node.text:
➖HACER O NO EJERCICIO SI ESTOY ENFERM@➖

Antes que nada quiero decir que esto es mi opinión de acuerdo a mi experiencia.

Muchas veces hemos escuchado el “haz ejercicio para que sudes la enfermedad” la verdad es que no es verdad la enfermedad no se puede sudar, obviamente, y no “la sacas” de esa forma.

MI OPINIÓN para tomar la desicion si hacer ejercicio o parar cuando estoy enferm@ es preguntarme como realmente me siento, si me siento mal, estoy cansada, o si yo se que necesito reposo PARO Y NO HAGO EJERCICIO.

El cuerpo puede estar con las defensas bajas y si yo hago ejercicio lo voy a debilitar más! Esto ocasionaría que mi recuperación sea MUCHO MÁS LENTA!

En conclusión, para mi es como una inversión, si nos queremos recuperar más rápido de una enfermedad debemos darle el tiempo a su cuerpo de solo hacer eso para sentirnos mejor después! No le están quitando una semana al cuerpo para estar en “mejor forma” al contrario, LE ESTÁN DANDO UNA SEMANA PARA QUE SANE! (Literal)

Cada persona, situación, malestar, enfermedad, prioridades o cualquier cosa pudieran ser diferentes por eso siempre les digo que se escuchen y de acuerdo a eso hagan lo que crean que sea más favorable para ustedes! Pero siempre priorizando su SALUD! 

Barby✨

.
.
.
